{"key":"processedPost-9978760","value":{"id":9978760,"first":9978625,"last":9979990,"when":1237174795,"utime":"03/16/09 06:39 AM","content":"First of all, it's a mistake to think the humidity is high just because you see condensation.&nbsp; Condensation forms on the warm side of any surface with a temperature differential across it.&nbsp; Condensation will form on the outside of a glass of iced tea in the middle of the desert when it's 100F outside and VERY low humidity.<br /><br />Second, fresh air exchange is the number 1 pinning trigger, and you don't get much fresh air in a sealed up tub.<br /><br />Third, unless you're living in an unheated igloo, you don't need an incubator.&nbsp; We just got another foot of snow today in the middle of March, yet I still colonize jars on an open shelf at normal room temperature.<br />RR","title":"Re: New way to keep rH high??","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}